25|$|On 14 November 2002, {{authorities}} in Ireland were {{cited by the}} European Court of Justice over the microbiological contamination of hundreds {{of public and private}} <b>water</b> <b>supplies.</b> The EU's Drinking Water Directive requires an absence of E. coli in drinking <b>water</b> <b>supplies</b> to protect human health.|$|R
